<head>
    <title>================= dl_manager =================</title>
</head>
<body>
    <section>
        <p>What is this:</p>
        <p>The best way of describe it is using it. <br/>With it you can: <ul>
            <li>Add new url to be downloaded on the server.</li>
            <li>Retrieve the downloaded files.</li>
            <li>Remove the urls you want.</li>
        </ul></p>
    </section>
    <section><p>Requirements</p>
    <p><ul>
        <li>Apache</li>
        <li>PHP (php extensions: json, curl, sqlite3)</li>
        <li>Python3 (Here I said Python3 cause I made with Python3 not cause I rely on any particular feature not available in previous versions. You will need to migrate dl_manager_service script if want to use Python2)</li>
        <li>Python3 modules: sqlite3, re, urllib, os, subprocess (I do know this are core python modules, but ...)</li>
        <li><a href="http://rg3.github.com/youtube-dl/">youtube-dl</a> to download video from youtube</li>
    </ul></p></section>
